radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal atelectasis at the lung bases; no pleural effusion, focal pulmonary nodule or mass. Normal imaged cardiac apex. The liver shows homogeneous parenchymal enhancement without suspicious focal lesion. Normal gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands. Symmetric enhancement and excretion of kidneys with punctate hypodensities suggestive of simple cysts. The appendix is dilated and fluid-filled with an appendicolith and associated fat stranding. No perforation or abscess. Decompressed colon without obstruction or inflammation. No bone destructive lesions or acute fractures.
